locality is situated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D6512C04CED40BA8EFD869FEC2010" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EFD869AE524A7" blockId="7.[226,1361,581,646]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC04CED40B8D4FD869D442440" box="[696,804,581,609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" unit="mm" value="7.2">7.2 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC04CED40BE2EFD869ACE2440" box="[1090,1198,581,609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: forebody dark-brown; abdomen blackish; legs and antennae pale-reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EFD5A9D622503" blockId="7.[226,1362,665,802]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">
Head (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04CED40BB51FD5A9FEF2494" box="[317,399,665,693]" captionStart="Figs 8-13" captionStartId="8.[226,276,1556,1581]" captionTargetBox="[226,1355,249,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[226,1360,249,1532]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 8-13: Lathrobium makaluicum nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11-12) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (13) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.5 mm; 13: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518397/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) 1.03 times as broad as long; punctation moderately coarse and rather sparse; interstices with distinct microreticulation. Eyes weakly projecting from lateral contours of head, approximately one third as long as postocular region in dorsal view and composed of approximately 30 ommatidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EFCF69FC825BB" blockId="7.[226,1361,821,922]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04CED40BB1EFCF69FDF2570" box="[370,447,821,849]" captionStart="Figs 8-13" captionStartId="8.[226,276,1556,1581]" captionTargetBox="[226,1355,249,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[226,1360,249,1532]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 8-13: Lathrobium makaluicum nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11-12) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (13) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.5 mm; 13: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518397/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) 1.18 times as long as broad and 1.02 times as broad as head; punctation similar to that of head; impunctate midline rather broad; interstices with microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EFC6E9C572233" blockId="7.[226,1361,941,1042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04CED40BB29FC6E9FF425E8" box="[325,404,941,969]" captionStart="Figs 8-13" captionStartId="8.[226,276,1556,1581]" captionTargetBox="[226,1355,249,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[226,1360,249,1532]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 8-13: Lathrobium makaluicum nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11-12) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (13) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.5 mm; 13: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518397/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) short, 0.53 times as long as pronotum; humeral angles weakly marked; punctation shallow and rather sparse; interstices without distinct microsculpture. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EFBE69A5A22AB" blockId="7.[226,1361,1061,1162]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Abdomen 1.1 times as broad as elytra; punctation fine and moderately dense, somewhat sparser on tergites VII-VIII than on tergites III-VI; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe; posterior margin of tergite VIII weakly convex.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EFB5F9A452023" blockId="7.[226,1362,1180,1538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">
♂: protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04CED40B9C4FB5E9D9A2298" box="[936,1018,1181,1209]" captionStart="Figs 8-13" captionStartId="8.[226,276,1556,1581]" captionTargetBox="[226,1355,249,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[226,1360,249,1532]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 8-13: Lathrobium makaluicum nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11-12) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (13) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.5 mm; 13: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518397/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse and with rather extensive postero-median impression, this impression with moderately modified stout black setae, posterior margin weakly concave; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04CED40BE07FB259AA92323" box="[1131,1225,1254,1282]" captionStart="Figs 8-13" captionStartId="8.[226,276,1556,1581]" captionTargetBox="[226,1355,249,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[226,1360,249,1532]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 8-13: Lathrobium makaluicum nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11-12) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (13) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.5 mm; 13: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518397/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse, middle with distinct longitudinal impression, this impression narrowly without setae along the middle, on either side of middle with extensive oblong cluster of numerous moderately modified stout black setae, posterior margin indistinctly concave in the middle; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04CED40B86FFABA9CF023B4" box="[515,656,1401,1429]" captionStart="Figs 8-13" captionStartId="8.[226,276,1556,1581]" captionTargetBox="[226,1355,249,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[226,1360,249,1532]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 8-13: Lathrobium makaluicum nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11-12) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (13) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.5 mm; 13: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518397/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Figs 11-13</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC04CED40B8C8FABA9D7523B4" box="[676,789,1401,1429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" unit="mm" value="1.15">1.15 mm</quantity>
long and symmetric; ventral process curved and apically very acute in lateral view, apex narrowly truncate in ventral view; dorsal plate with moderately long and lamellate apical portion, and with short, weakly sclerotized basal portion; internal sac with dark membranous structures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EF9D89FEC2010" blockId="7.[226,396,1557,1591]" box="[226,396,1557,1591]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">
<specimenCount id="9D31FD10C04CED40BA8EF9D89E9C2016" box="[226,252,1563,1591]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D6512C04CED40BA8EF9879A85211D" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B883699C04CED40BA8EF9879A85211D" blockId="7.[226,1361,1604,1852]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">
Comparative notes: Based on the external (habitus, coloration, presence of microsculpture on the pronotum) and the male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04CED40BE3AF9AB9B7920A5" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[1110,1305,1640,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makaluicum">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04CED40BE3AF9AB9B7920A5" box="[1110,1305,1640,1668]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">L. makaluicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
undoubtedly belongs to the 
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04CED40B849F94E9CA52088" box="[549,709,1677,1705]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">L. nepalense</emphasis>
group. In the key in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64B68C04CED40B9B8F94E9AC32088" author="ASSING V" box="[980,1187,1677,1705]" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" pagination="142 - 209" refId="ref8996" refString="ASSING V. (2012 b): A revision of the Lathrobium species of the Himalaya (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonn Zoological Bulletin 61 (2): 142 - 209." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING (2012b)</bibRefCitation>
, it would key out at couplet 13, together with the externally similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04CED40B9CBF9719A3520EF" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[935,1109,1714,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diremptum">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04CED40B9CBF9719A3520EF" box="[935,1109,1714,1742]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">L. diremptum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04CED40BEF5F9719B3120EF" box="[1177,1361,1714,1742]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">L. bibarbatum</emphasis>
from Taplejung district in eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3207609C04CED40B8C4F9159C9820D3" box="[680,760,1750,1778]" name="Nepal" pageId="7" pageNumber="254">Nepal</collectingCountry>
. It is distinguished from these species by the different shape and chaetotaxy of the male sternite VIII and by the different morphology of the aedeagus (shape of ventral process and of dorsal plate; internal structures).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
